race.comment: LIGHT FILLED (3) raced handy and looked the winner at the furlong but was edged out late on debut over 1000m at this track 18 days ago. Has an extra 400m to negotiate but with that run under her belt she looks sure to be in the finish again. MISS DECEIVER (5) did some work early then was out-sprinted over the final stages at Moonee Valley last time out. Nicely placed over an extra furlong today and with a soft run assured from gate one she makes plenty of appeal. SKETCH (9) returned from a spell and had her first run for the Freedman stable when an eye-catching second over 1200m at Kilmore recently. Sure to appreciate the longer journey and is right in the mix. NOSTRA BELLA (6) returns from a 195-day spell. Best of five runs in the maiden prep was a 3.1 length defeat in the Group 3 Thoroughbred Breeders at Flemington. No surprise if she produced a big run while fresh. COOLAZCLARA (1) has been about the mark at both runs this prep and is one for the exotics.
